1
00:00:25,240 --> 00:00:26,520
<i>Breathe in...</i>

2
00:00:27,160 --> 00:00:28,320
<i>...and out.</i>

3
00:00:32,520 --> 00:00:35,760
<i>Let the wave of calm</i>
<i>wash over you.</i>

4
00:00:36,640 --> 00:00:39,560
<i>Feel your stress melt away.</i>

5
00:00:42,080 --> 00:00:44,600
<i>Let go of things</i>
<i>beyond your control.</i>

6
00:00:48,560 --> 00:00:50,240
<i>Focus on your breath...</i>

7
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:55,440
<i>...your heartbeat.</i>

8
00:01:04,560 --> 00:01:07,520
<i>Stay present in this moment.</i>

9
00:01:08,520 --> 00:01:11,760
<i>Let everything else</i>
<i>just disappear.</i>

10
00:01:27,520 --> 00:01:28,800
Hands to heart.

11
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:31,440
Just wing it through.

12
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:33,400
And warrior.

13
00:01:37,960 --> 00:01:39,080
Warrior two.

14
00:01:39,320 --> 00:01:41,560
Then reach into the back
of the room, that's right.

15
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:43,880
Reaching, reaching
into the back of the room.

16
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:45,320
Reach.

17
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:52,000
Side.

18
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:54,800
Strong over your front half.

19
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:56,640
Bend.

20
00:01:58,200 --> 00:02:01,680
All right. Coming through.
You can jump up or walk up.

21
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:04,520
And inhale.

22
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:08,840
Your heart is alive.

23
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:11,000
And exhale.

24
00:02:14,040 --> 00:02:15,480
Come back to center.

25
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:17,040
Hands to heart.

26
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:19,600
Feel your body vibrating.

27
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:21,200
You're all one,...

28
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:23,520
...you're all here,...

29
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:27,120
...in your body
and in your power.

30
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:34,360
Thank you for joining me
this morning.

31
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:36,600
May it bring peace
to the rest of your day.

32
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:38,480
And may the merit
of our practice...

33
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:41,200
...be dedicated to all beings
everywhere.

34
00:02:41,880 --> 00:02:43,360
I honor the light in you.

35
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:46,080
<i>-Namaste.</i>
<i>-Namaste.</i>

36
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,360
I honor the light within you.

37
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:53,400
<i>-Namaste.</i>
<i>-Namaste.</i>

38
00:02:58,680 --> 00:02:59,800
-That was amazing.
-All right.

39
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:01,240
Reel it in, teacher's pet.

40
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:03,480
You're just mad because you can't
even get through the flow.

41
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:06,080
Are you kidding?
I mastered a bunch of poses.

42
00:03:06,480 --> 00:03:08,240
Oh, child's pose doesn't count.

43
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:09,640
So how was class?

44
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:12,080
It was perfect, as always.

45
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:15,240
I'm sure it was for you,
but I'm wondering about Charlie.

46
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:17,800
Me? Well, killed it as always.

47
00:03:18,640 --> 00:03:19,800
All right, fine.

48
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:21,120
It kinda killed me.

49
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:24,080
That's right, that's why they
call it a practice, honey.

50
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:26,720
Don't worry, we'll have your body
cleansed in no time.

51
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:27,840
Thanks, mom.

52
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:30,960
All right, sweaty. Shall we?

53
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:33,040
-We shall. Thank you.
-Okay.

54
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:34,920
You're welcome.
I'll see you soon.

55
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:39,880
<i>Another breath in...</i>

56
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:42,040
<i>...and out.</i>

57
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,240
<i>Let go.</i>

58
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:50,920
<i>It takes no effort</i>
<i>to simply let go.</i>

59
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:54,720
Maybe for you.

60
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:11,520
-Thank you.
-You're home today.

61
00:04:12,440 --> 00:04:13,640
-Okay, I'll see you next week.
-See you.

62
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:14,560
Yeah.

63
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:22,120
Aunt Amanda.

64
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:24,480
-Hey.
-Charlie.

65
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:25,520
-Good to see you.
-How are you?

66
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:26,960
Look at you.

67
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:30,520
I can't believe you're here.

68
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:33,080
-Hey.
-It's so good to see you.

69
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:34,600
You, too.

70
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,240
You, too, sis.

71
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:40,480
Autumn crocuses.
Are those for me?

72
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:42,160
Well, you're literally
the only person I know...

73
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:43,360
...who likes these.

74
00:04:44,080 --> 00:04:45,240
They're beautiful.

75
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:47,480
Let me just wash up,
I've been teaching all morning.

76
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:48,920
But please, come in.

77
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:50,120
-Take a look around.
-Hey.

78
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:52,280
Wow, she's really fixed up
the place.

79
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:53,520
Yeah, you know mom,...

80
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:54,480
...everything
had to be perfect...

81
00:04:54,520 --> 00:04:55,840
...for the grand reopening
this weekend.

82
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:58,120
Wanted to give the place
a rebirth.

83
00:04:58,160 --> 00:04:59,920
-Her words, not mine.
-Yeah.

84
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:03,400
Well, speaking of rebirth,
you're like a new man.

85
00:05:03,440 --> 00:05:04,320
Thank you.

86
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:05,920
Last time I saw you, you...

87
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:07,920
It's okay, I know.
You can say it.

88
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:09,120
I relapsed.

89
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:11,360
But I've got three years sober
next week.

90
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:12,720
-Good for you.
-Thank you.

91
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:14,880
-Oh, I'm proud of you.
-Thanks.

92
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:16,400
It really ought to do
with my mom.

93
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:18,800
Ever since I've been back,
she's been keeping an eye on me.

94
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:20,240
Well, her and Maya.

95
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,080
Maya?

96
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:25,600
Maya is my mom's assistant
slash star pupil...

97
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:27,200
...slash spiritual successor.

98
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:28,520
The yin to my mom's yang.

99
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:30,200
Oh, and she's my girlfriend.

100
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:31,320
It's her right there.

101
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:35,360
Wow, she certainly seems limber.

102
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:37,520
She's been taking
mom's classes for years.

103
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,920
Even before
she started working here.

104
00:05:38,960 --> 00:05:40,040
It's actually how we met.

105
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:41,840
She's so great. Come on.

106
00:05:42,520 --> 00:05:44,720
She's smart, she's funny.

107
00:05:44,760 --> 00:05:46,720
She helped my mom
renovate this entire place.

108
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:48,240
Come on, I'll introduce you.

109
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:50,960
Hey, Maya. Maya.

110
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:52,280
Maya.

111
00:05:57,960 --> 00:05:59,080
Charlie, oh, my gosh.

112
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:00,160
You almost gave me
a heart attack.

113
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,160
I couldn't help it.

114
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:02,640
It is my fault, really.

115
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:05,440
I intend to encourage
his juvenile impulses.

116
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:08,480
I'm Amanda. Lauren's sister.

117
00:06:08,520 --> 00:06:11,080
Oh, my gosh.
Why didn't you say so?

118
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:12,440
Sorry. I'm just really excited.

119
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:14,320
Lauren's told me
so much about you.

120
00:06:14,360 --> 00:06:16,960
Social-media consultant,
from New York, right?

121
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:19,000
Well, I have only been
in New York...

122
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:21,760
...for a few years,
but that's me, yeah.

123
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:24,400
Pretty much the polar opposite
of my tree-hugging sister.

124
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:26,640
Oh, that's okay.
I won't hold it against you.

125
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,440
I was just kidding. Bad joke.

126
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:30,200
Your sister is kind of my hero.

127
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:31,640
Maya's one
restraining order away...

128
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:33,200
...from being
a full-fledged stalker.

129
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:36,480
Well, I'm so glad that you
could come out for the reopening.

130
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:38,600
I know Lauren
was really hoping that you would.

131
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:39,800
I wouldn't miss it.

132
00:06:40,280 --> 00:06:41,640
Good.
How long are you in town for?

133
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:44,640
Not sure.
I just finished a campaign,...

134
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:46,640
...so I was thinking of
taking a little time off...

135
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:47,840
...before my next gig.

136
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:51,040
You'd be amazed how easy it is
to sublet in Manhattan.

137
00:06:51,440 --> 00:06:53,320
But it looks like you guys
have been really busy.

138
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:55,000
I mean,
I barely recognize the place.

139
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:57,080
I know. Can you believe
this is even the same building?

140
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:59,600
Your parents' health center
was an amazing foundation.

141
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:03,040
And then Lauren's vision just
helped it become fully realized.

142
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:04,320
I'm sure it's a lot to take in...

143
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:06,400
...after being away
for three years, but...

144
00:07:08,320 --> 00:07:09,200
What's wrong?

145
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:12,520
-Did I say something?
-No. No, it's nothing.

146
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:13,960
It's fine, really.

147
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:15,080
Okay.

148
00:07:15,880 --> 00:07:17,160
Why don't we find mom?

149
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,760
We'll give you
the, well, grand tour.

150
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:20,040
-Great idea.
-All right.

151
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:23,560
I didn't mean to upset her.

152
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:24,920
No, don't worry about it.
It's just...

153
00:07:24,960 --> 00:07:26,240
It's a touchy subject is all.

154
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:27,560
-Okay.
-It's all good.

155
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,720
-Okay.
-All right?

156
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:36,720
Ian?

157
00:07:37,320 --> 00:07:38,200
Amanda.

158
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:40,000
It's wonderful to see you.

159
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:43,240
Lauren's been talking about you
nonstop.

160
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:46,520
Welcome to our new
and growing family business.

161
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:50,200
-Hey, kids.
-Hey, pop.

162
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:51,480
Have you seen mom?

163
00:07:51,520 --> 00:07:52,920
We're hoping to give Amanda
the tour.

164
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:55,400
No, but I'll get
out of your hair.

165
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:57,240
See you at the house for dinner?

166
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:09,600
Here we are. Home sweet home.

167
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:14,600
You updated the house.

168
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:16,880
Business must really be booming.

169
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:19,600
It will be. Just have to pay off
the loans first.

170
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:21,760
Don't worry, we'll more than
make up the difference.

171
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:23,120
We have big plans.

172
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:24,680
Come on.

173
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:29,000
Remember this room?

174
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:34,040
Even my old room gets a makeover.

175
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:39,040
Re-gifting my flowers already?

176
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:40,880
Oh, I thought
it was a nice touch.

177
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:48,760
Simpler times.

178
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:51,000
After you moved out,...

179
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:53,400
...we figured your bedroom
shouldn't just collect dust.

180
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:57,520
Now it's the perfect getaway
in addition to the guesthouse.

181
00:08:57,680 --> 00:08:59,840
But Charlie
has officially taken that over.

182
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:01,760
And Maya
has all but moved in, too.

183
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,440
Look, Amanda,...

184
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:06,840
...if you ever wanted
to take a little break...

185
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:08,640
...from the East Coast
for a while...

186
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:10,840
I appreciate that.

187
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:12,560
Really, I do.

188
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:15,440
And the sound of being here
for even just a little while...

189
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:17,280
...does sound good, but...

190
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:18,440
Then what's stopping you?

191
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:19,360
You work remotely.

192
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:21,400
You don't need to be
across the country.

193
00:09:21,680 --> 00:09:22,800
Come home.

194
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:25,880
I don't know
if it would be the best idea.

195
00:09:27,280 --> 00:09:28,440
You're still mad at him?

196
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:30,080
After all these years?

197
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:31,600
Lauren...

198
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:34,520
...I know you never believed me.

199
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:36,920
And I know you don't wanna think
he had an affair.

200
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:38,960
I wish I was wrong.

201
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:41,320
But I know what I saw.

202
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:42,480
And...

203
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:45,080
...I'll never forgive Ian.

204
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:52,800
Think about it.

205
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:55,680
I didn't invite you back here
just for the reopening.

206
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:58,360
Come on,
I wanna show you something.

207
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:02,440
Follow me.

208
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:11,840
I've been learning about
the healing properties of plants.

209
00:10:12,520 --> 00:10:14,960
Well, you've always loved
flowers.

210
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:18,720
Well, many are quite medicinal.
They're nature's pharmacy.

211
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:22,600
I miss you.

212
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:24,560
I want to give us another chance.

213
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:27,520
We were so close.

214
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:30,000
Your entire life was here.

215
00:10:31,280 --> 00:10:33,920
Are we gonna throw all that away
just because of a few bad years?

216
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:35,240
I've missed you, too.

217
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:38,000
Then, please, come back home.

218
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:39,960
Let's be a family again.

219
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,120
Do you wanna plant the last one?

220
00:11:37,040 --> 00:11:38,480
-Boo!
-Maya!

221
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:40,360
-Not cool.
-Yes.

222
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:41,640
Well, that's what you get...

223
00:11:41,680 --> 00:11:43,720
...for that little gong stunt
earlier.

224
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,080
Oh, what's wrong?

225
00:11:48,520 --> 00:11:49,400
The baby can dish it,...

226
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:50,720
-...but he can't take it?
-Okay.

227
00:11:56,560 --> 00:11:57,840
Is that better?

228
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:01,720
Good.

229
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:05,560
-I have to get ready for dinner.
-What...?

230
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:08,280
What am I supposed to do?

231
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:10,320
Well, you can start
by getting dressed.

232
00:12:10,760 --> 00:12:13,280
That's the opposite
of how I thought this was going.

233
00:12:13,320 --> 00:12:14,600
You know,
I couldn't help but notice...

234
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:16,360
...things have been
a little bit intense...

235
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:17,720
...with Amanda being back.

236
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:18,720
Yeah.

237
00:12:19,120 --> 00:12:21,680
Yeah, I know. I was kinda hoping
things between her and my dad...

238
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:23,120
...would've cooled off
by now, but...

239
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:25,080
But not quite so, I see.

240
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,920
Well, from what you told me,
I can't really blame her.

241
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:31,560
Is she still mad at him
for what he did?

242
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:33,040
Well, what she thinks he did.

243
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:34,920
-Yeah.
-She never did prove it.

244
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:37,320
Mom doesn't believe it.
Never did.

245
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:39,880
What about you?

246
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:41,840
I don't know.

247
00:12:42,760 --> 00:12:46,040
I mean, dad's a charmer.
But cheating on mom? I mean...

248
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:49,160
...whatever Aunt Amanda
thinks he did...

249
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:51,080
...was enough
to make her leave, so,...

250
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:54,840
...I hope we can all just
put it behind us, start fresh.

251
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:56,600
Me, too.

252
00:12:57,440 --> 00:12:59,680
I just don't wanna see you
get hurt again.

253
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:01,560
Or Lauren.

254
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:03,080
One thing is for certain.

255
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:06,520
-Dinner's gonna be super awkward.
-Super awkward.

256
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:09,840
So you better hurry up
and go get dressed.

257
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:11,480
All right.

258
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:14,600
I'm not gonna say no
to a lady with a bat.

259
00:13:19,680 --> 00:13:21,600
Amanda, do you like the tofu?

260
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:24,600
This is tofu?

261
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:28,280
-It's great. It's very...
-Chewy?

262
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:29,200
Hey.

263
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:32,640
It's Maya's recipe.
She's been cooking for us.

264
00:13:32,680 --> 00:13:34,120
In addition to everything else.

265
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:36,280
Yeah, Maya's been a real Godsend.

266
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:42,120
So, I have an announcement.

267
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:46,640
We all know that
the grand reopening...

268
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:48,160
...is just a few days away.

269
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:51,840
It's a big step
for the wellness center.

270
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:54,520
Almost a rebirth.

271
00:13:55,760 --> 00:13:57,880
We're expanding a lot.

272
00:13:57,920 --> 00:14:00,000
And in addition
to all the new services...

273
00:14:00,040 --> 00:14:01,600
...and amenities
we'll be providing,...

274
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:04,000
...Maya and I have been working
on my brand.

275
00:14:04,120 --> 00:14:06,480
Reaching more people
outside of the studio.

276
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:09,360
Expanding
my social-media presence.

277
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:13,840
Now, Amanda,
this is your area of expertise.

278
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:16,680
And since you don't currently
have a client,...

279
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:19,560
...I would like to officially
invite you...

280
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:21,760
...into the fold
as my business partner.

281
00:14:22,040 --> 00:14:23,560
-Wait, what?
-Really?

282
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:25,920
That's awesome, now you can
move back, like, for good.

283
00:14:26,120 --> 00:14:27,640
I know it's asking a lot.

284
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,920
But mom and dad
always wanted this...

285
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:31,960
...to be a family business.

286
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:33,840
They left it to the both of us.

287
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,440
Lauren, isn't this something...

288
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:36,960
...we should be talking about
in private?

289
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:38,320
I mean, there are other people...

290
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:39,840
...who have a vested interest
in the business,...

291
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:41,720
...people that should have a say.

292
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:43,040
Hey, no offense.

293
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:46,640
We all know
there's a lot of history here,...

294
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:51,160
...but I want to change that
to make things right.

295
00:14:51,720 --> 00:14:53,680
The two of you
have nothing to worry about.

296
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:55,840
I'll still need you.
That won't change.

297
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:58,520
Yeah, I mean, it's your decision.

298
00:14:58,680 --> 00:15:00,920
No, it's not. It's our decision.

299
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:03,040
Dad, come on,
this is a good thing.

300
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:04,840
Charlie, will you stay
out of this, all right?

301
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:06,360
You know what happened last time
that Amanda came here.

302
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:07,600
-Enough! Enough!
-Really?

303
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:10,840
This is my business.

304
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:12,080
I built it.

305
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:13,720
I'm the one who took over
the center...

306
00:15:13,760 --> 00:15:14,760
...when no one else wanted it,...

307
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:16,800
...so the only opinions
I'm interested in...

308
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:19,880
...on the subject are mine
and my sister's.

309
00:15:20,080 --> 00:15:20,960
Yeah.

310
00:15:21,920 --> 00:15:22,800
Yeah.

311
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:24,000
It's fine.

312
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:27,440
Now, Amanda,...

313
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:30,280
...I don't expect you
to answer right away.

314
00:15:30,440 --> 00:15:31,920
Take as long as you need.

315
00:15:32,520 --> 00:15:35,120
But just know that you always
have a home here.

316
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:36,760
And nothing
would make me happier...

317
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:38,600
...than having you back
in our lives.

318
00:15:42,160 --> 00:15:43,080
Okay.

319
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:44,760
I'll think about it.

320
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:46,240
Good.

321
00:15:47,720 --> 00:15:49,760
Well, if you'll excuse me.

322
00:16:00,040 --> 00:16:00,960
I just don't understand...

323
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:02,600
...how you couldn't
discuss this with me.

324
00:16:02,680 --> 00:16:04,600
It's one thing for her
to come back here for a week.

325
00:16:04,640 --> 00:16:06,080
But actually live here?

326
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:07,640
And to own half the business?

327
00:16:07,680 --> 00:16:10,000
I am trying to make things right.
She is my sister.

328
00:16:10,040 --> 00:16:12,600
-She deserves that much.
-I don't care who she is.

329
00:16:12,640 --> 00:16:14,040
You never discussed it.

330
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:15,960
I knew coming back here
was a mistake.

331
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,600
Hey, don't say that.

332
00:16:17,640 --> 00:16:19,360
-Oh, like it even matters?
-I'm glad you're here, okay?

333
00:16:19,880 --> 00:16:20,960
Thanks, Charlie.

334
00:16:21,520 --> 00:16:23,160
Oh, my gosh.
Yeah, just walk away.

335
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:25,640
And I'm sorry
about all this, Maya.

336
00:16:25,680 --> 00:16:27,360
I'm sure Charlie's told you...

337
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:29,560
...about the fallout
the family had before.

338
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:32,960
Yeah. Yeah, he did.

339
00:16:33,280 --> 00:16:35,800
The way they're fighting,
it's almost like you never left.

340
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:40,760
I'm sorry.

341
00:16:42,120 --> 00:16:43,160
I didn't mean it.

342
00:16:44,680 --> 00:16:47,440
It's just,
Lauren and I have been...

343
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:50,600
...such a great team
the past few months.

344
00:16:50,640 --> 00:16:54,560
I'm just a little hurt
she never brought it up to me.

345
00:16:55,360 --> 00:16:56,240
That's all.

346
00:16:57,400 --> 00:16:58,720
It's okay.

347
00:16:59,280 --> 00:17:00,280
I understand.

348
00:17:00,400 --> 00:17:03,160
I better get ready for bed.

349
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,080
It's...

350
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:05,840
...the big day tomorrow.

351
00:17:05,880 --> 00:17:07,200
-So...
-Yeah.

352
00:17:07,240 --> 00:17:08,160
It's a good idea.

353
00:17:08,880 --> 00:17:10,640
-You ready to turn in?
-Oh, no.

354
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:12,800
No, I'm gonna stay up
for a little while.

355
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:16,920
Brew Lauren some herbal tea,
help her relax.

356
00:17:17,320 --> 00:17:18,520
I know
it doesn't seem like it,...

357
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:21,560
...but she's really nervous
about the reopening tomorrow.

358
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:25,000
Thank you so much
for taking care of her.

359
00:17:25,040 --> 00:17:25,920
Please.

360
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:28,920
It's the least I can do.
I'd be lost without her, so...

361
00:17:30,040 --> 00:17:30,920
Goodnight.

362
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:34,200
All right.
Well, see you in a bit.

363
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:35,120
Yeah.

364
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:04,160
Everything okay?

365
00:18:05,120 --> 00:18:06,000
Lauren's...

366
00:18:06,520 --> 00:18:08,040
...cutting it awful close.

367
00:18:08,280 --> 00:18:09,640
Her speech is in five minutes.

368
00:18:11,040 --> 00:18:12,960
-Hey. Have you seen mom?
-Hey.

369
00:18:13,240 --> 00:18:14,760
-What, she's not back yet?
-No.

370
00:18:15,720 --> 00:18:16,880
Last time I saw her, she said...

371
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:18,000
...she was feeling
a little nauseous,...

372
00:18:18,040 --> 00:18:19,920
...but that was, like,
a half hour ago.

373
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:21,200
Yeah, she said
she hasn't been feeling well...

374
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:22,440
...the last couple of days.

375
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:24,720
I think the reopening's
making her a little bit nervous.

376
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:25,960
I'm gonna go check the restroom.

377
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:27,320
-Yeah.
-I'll go with you.

378
00:18:31,280 --> 00:18:33,720
I'll get another tray out
and try to stall.

379
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:35,360
-Okay.
-Thank you, Rebecca.

380
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:45,880
Oh, my gosh. Are you okay?

381
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:48,920
I'm fine. Just nerves, I guess.

382
00:18:49,120 --> 00:18:52,080
Hey, you don't have to do this
if you're not feeling up to it.

383
00:18:52,120 --> 00:18:54,200
No, Amanda's right.
I mean, we can postpone.

384
00:18:54,560 --> 00:18:55,760
Or I could give the speech
if you want.

385
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:57,880
I mean, I basically memorized it
while I was helping you prep.

386
00:18:57,920 --> 00:19:00,440
Oh, no, thank you.

387
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:02,280
I'm fine.

388
00:19:02,680 --> 00:19:04,560
This is everything
that we've been working for.

389
00:19:04,600 --> 00:19:05,920
I need to do this.

390
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:09,240
Trust me, I'm fine.
I've got this.

391
00:19:09,520 --> 00:19:10,400
Let's go.

392
00:19:22,360 --> 00:19:23,720
Good morning, everyone.

393
00:19:23,880 --> 00:19:26,960
Thank you so much for coming out
to support us today.

394
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,520
It is my pleasure
to introduce to you...

395
00:19:29,560 --> 00:19:31,600
...the woman
responsible for all of this,...

396
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:34,240
...the guru that you all know
and love.

397
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:37,720
Please put your hands together
for Dr. Lauren Birch.

398
00:19:41,560 --> 00:19:42,800
Thank you, Maya.

399
00:19:42,840 --> 00:19:44,080
As many of you know,...

400
00:19:44,120 --> 00:19:45,960
...Maya has been my rock
in all of this.

401
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:48,400
And this would not have been
possible without her.

402
00:19:48,960 --> 00:19:50,800
When my parents first opened...

403
00:19:50,840 --> 00:19:52,960
...the Birch Springs
Family Health Center,...

404
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:55,400
...they had a very simple
mission in mind.

405
00:19:56,480 --> 00:19:57,360
You okay?

406
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:00,320
I'm fine.

407
00:20:00,680 --> 00:20:03,080
Sorry, I recently switched
from coffee to tea,...

408
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:05,400
...and my brain
has not forgiven me yet.

409
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:10,760
The mission they began
was to provide the community...

410
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:12,720
...with a center for healing.

411
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:15,760
A place of comfort,
a place of joy.

412
00:20:15,960 --> 00:20:20,080
And that's a mission I've strived
to live up to my entire...

413
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:24,280
-Lauren, Lauren, you okay?
-Mom. Mom.

414
00:20:24,320 --> 00:20:25,840
Lauren?

415
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:27,240
-Mom.
-Lauren!

416
00:20:27,280 --> 00:20:28,320
-Lauren?
-Lauren?

417
00:20:28,360 --> 00:20:29,480
-You okay?
-Lauren!

418
00:20:29,520 --> 00:20:31,320
-Lauren, you okay?
-Mom.

419
00:20:32,360 --> 00:20:33,640
Lauren, Lauren?

420
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:35,640
Somebody call 911!

421
00:20:35,760 --> 00:20:37,160
-Mom.
-Lauren. Lauren?

422
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:38,960
Lauren? Lauren!

423
00:20:55,720 --> 00:20:57,600
We will all remember
her warmth...

424
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:00,280
...her sense of humor...

425
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:03,000
...and her caring spirit.

426
00:21:05,880 --> 00:21:07,440
And her spirit will endure.

427
00:21:08,440 --> 00:21:10,840
What she's built
is a testament...

428
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:13,120
...to who she was.

429
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:16,520
Her mission was to heal.

430
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:22,080
Lauren cared about the health,
personal growth of others,...

431
00:21:22,120 --> 00:21:23,760
...almost more than herself.

432
00:21:24,440 --> 00:21:26,760
That compassion
is what I loved about her.

433
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:28,560
That's what we all loved
about her.

434
00:21:29,920 --> 00:21:31,600
She's left a hole in me.

435
00:21:32,840 --> 00:21:34,080
She would want us to heal.

436
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:37,400
And right now
I'm in dire need of healing.

437
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:40,000
I think we all are.

438
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:54,080
Thank you all for coming today
to Lauren's celebration.

439
00:21:54,640 --> 00:21:55,560
She would've loved that.

440
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:22,320
I'm so sorry, Amanda.

441
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:24,960
Josh? Josh Stone?

442
00:22:25,880 --> 00:22:28,880
-I haven't seen you since...
-High school.

443
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:30,120
Yeah.

444
00:22:30,520 --> 00:22:31,400
You doing okay?

445
00:22:33,320 --> 00:22:35,560
Spent the entire past week
crying.

446
00:22:35,600 --> 00:22:38,280
So I just, I feel like
I don't have any tears left.

447
00:22:39,280 --> 00:22:40,160
Well...

448
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:42,560
Just in case.

449
00:22:45,360 --> 00:22:47,240
It's just so bizarre.

450
00:22:47,560 --> 00:22:50,360
Lauren was one of the healthiest
people I know to...

451
00:22:51,760 --> 00:22:53,320
...she just collapse
like that,...

452
00:22:53,360 --> 00:22:55,280
...I mean, from heart failure?

453
00:22:55,920 --> 00:22:56,800
Yeah, I know.

454
00:22:57,280 --> 00:22:58,480
It doesn't make sense.

455
00:23:10,120 --> 00:23:12,320
When was the last time
you saw Lauren?

456
00:23:12,840 --> 00:23:14,960
I'm sorry,
I don't mean to be rude.

457
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:17,680
It's just, I wasn't expecting
my high school boyfriend...

458
00:23:17,720 --> 00:23:19,560
...to be at her memorial.

459
00:23:19,680 --> 00:23:21,880
Lauren and I actually reconnected
a few years ago.

460
00:23:22,720 --> 00:23:23,600
You did?

461
00:23:24,080 --> 00:23:26,040
Yeah, someone broke
into the center,...

462
00:23:26,080 --> 00:23:27,280
...vandalized the place.

463
00:23:27,600 --> 00:23:29,160
She came down to the station
to give a statement,...

464
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:31,040
...and I bumped into her there.

465
00:23:31,360 --> 00:23:33,640
The station? What, you're a cop?

466
00:23:33,840 --> 00:23:35,480
Detective, actually.

467
00:23:35,800 --> 00:23:36,680
Homicide.

468
00:23:40,840 --> 00:23:41,920
I'll let you be.

469
00:23:42,320 --> 00:23:45,160
I just wanted to express
my condolences.

470
00:23:45,320 --> 00:23:48,440
Anything I can do to help,
even if it's just to talk...

471
00:23:49,080 --> 00:23:50,160
...don't hesitate to call.

472
00:23:52,240 --> 00:23:53,320
Thanks, Josh.

473
00:23:53,960 --> 00:23:56,200
Oh, can you do me a favor?

474
00:23:56,400 --> 00:23:58,280
Can you let Ian know
that it'll be a few days...

475
00:23:58,320 --> 00:24:00,280
...before the toxicology report
comes back?

476
00:24:00,720 --> 00:24:03,240
The toxicology report? What?

477
00:24:03,520 --> 00:24:06,560
Yeah, the autopsy
didn't give us much info...

478
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:07,720
...beyond heart failure,...

479
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:09,800
...so the lab performed
a toxicology report.

480
00:24:09,840 --> 00:24:12,400
Which, it's standard
in a case like this,...

481
00:24:12,440 --> 00:24:14,760
...to help identify
the cause of death...

482
00:24:14,800 --> 00:24:17,480
...and possibly identify
any contaminants in the system.

483
00:24:17,640 --> 00:24:20,040
Ian was anxious
to hear the results.

484
00:24:20,360 --> 00:24:22,560
Yeah, no, of course.
I'll let him know.

485
00:24:22,600 --> 00:24:23,480
Yeah.

486
00:24:24,360 --> 00:24:25,240
Thank you.

487
00:24:36,160 --> 00:24:37,920
I'm sorry for your loss.

488
00:24:38,160 --> 00:24:39,440
-Thanks.
-Of course.

489
00:24:39,480 --> 00:24:41,680
-I appreciate it.
-Thanks for having me. Take care.

490
00:24:41,720 --> 00:24:42,600
Thank you.

491
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:53,560
What a disaster.

492
00:24:53,640 --> 00:24:55,920
Charlie making
a complete arse out of himself.

493
00:24:56,080 --> 00:24:57,680
Three years sober, gone.

494
00:24:58,160 --> 00:24:59,240
What do you expect?

495
00:24:59,280 --> 00:25:01,560
He's a recovering addict.
And his mother just died.

496
00:25:01,600 --> 00:25:02,960
Yeah, of course,
you'd defend him.

497
00:25:03,160 --> 00:25:06,000
Are you kidding me? You're really
bringing this up now?

498
00:25:07,760 --> 00:25:09,000
She's gone, Amanda.

499
00:25:09,560 --> 00:25:11,440
We don't have to pretend
to get along anymore.

500
00:25:12,360 --> 00:25:14,280
Even though I know you still
blame me for what happened.

501
00:25:14,880 --> 00:25:16,160
I'm gonna go check on Charlie.

502
00:25:18,320 --> 00:25:19,920
Of course, I blame you.

503
00:25:19,960 --> 00:25:21,160
You cheated on her.

504
00:25:21,720 --> 00:25:23,360
How many times
do I have to tell you?

505
00:25:23,880 --> 00:25:25,200
Nothing happened.

506
00:25:25,720 --> 00:25:26,960
It's all in your head.

507
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:29,240
Lauren understood that.
Why can't you?

508
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:32,280
I know what I saw, and so do you.

509
00:25:33,080 --> 00:25:34,280
You and that girl
at the studio,...

510
00:25:34,320 --> 00:25:35,640
...when you thought no one
was looking.

511
00:25:35,680 --> 00:25:37,720
My gosh, would you just
let it go?

512
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:39,440
Lauren is dead.

513
00:25:41,080 --> 00:25:42,920
Do you really need
to keep ruining our lives?

514
00:25:44,160 --> 00:25:47,080
-You think I ruined your life?
-Of course, I do!

515
00:25:48,040 --> 00:25:49,680
You nearly ended my marriage,...

516
00:25:50,040 --> 00:25:51,600
...you sank our business,...

517
00:25:52,160 --> 00:25:53,080
...tore our family apart...

518
00:25:53,120 --> 00:25:54,720
...by pushing Charlie back
into using...

519
00:25:54,760 --> 00:25:57,480
