00:56:29,600 --> 00:56:31,600
...you're telling me somebody
snuck in...

1030
00:56:31,640 --> 00:56:33,240
...and tried to kill him
while he slept?

1031
00:56:33,440 --> 00:56:34,760
I know it sounds crazy.

1032
00:56:35,200 --> 00:56:36,080
-No.
-What...

1033
00:56:36,120 --> 00:56:37,480
It doesn't sound crazy to me.

1034
00:56:39,360 --> 00:56:41,360
Well, we have an officer
stationed outside his room.

1035
00:56:41,400 --> 00:56:43,840
Only authorized personnel
will get in from now on.

1036
00:56:43,960 --> 00:56:45,240
What about family?

1037
00:56:45,280 --> 00:56:46,160
I'm sorry.

1038
00:56:46,520 --> 00:56:47,720
I can't let you see him.

1039
00:56:48,320 --> 00:56:50,600
Charlie was targeted in much
the same way his mother was.

1040
00:56:51,080 --> 00:56:52,960
The only obvious conclusion
I can draw from that...

1041
00:56:53,000 --> 00:56:56,600
...is that Charlie's attacker is
responsible for Lauren's death.

1042
00:56:57,240 --> 00:56:58,920
This is now
a murder investigation.

1043
00:57:02,160 --> 00:57:04,160
Yeah, so...so,
so what happens now?

1044
00:57:04,200 --> 00:57:06,320
You three are
the closest people...

1045
00:57:06,360 --> 00:57:08,960
...in both Charlie
and Lauren's lives.

1046
00:57:09,600 --> 00:57:11,960
So you'll be brought in
for questioning.

1047
00:57:12,000 --> 00:57:13,080
What are you saying?

1048
00:57:13,600 --> 00:57:14,800
We're suspects?

1049
00:57:15,800 --> 00:57:16,680
Yes.

1050
00:57:16,920 --> 00:57:18,800
And you're the only ones
we've got.

1051
00:57:20,040 --> 00:57:22,200
But before we do all that,...

1052
00:57:22,960 --> 00:57:24,280
...I'm gonna go check on Charlie.

1053
00:57:25,760 --> 00:57:26,640
Thank you.

1054
00:57:46,280 --> 00:57:47,320
Detective?

1055
00:57:49,080 --> 00:57:49,960
Hey.

1056
00:57:50,160 --> 00:57:51,560
-What happened?
-Charlie, how...

1057
00:57:53,040 --> 00:57:54,000
How are you feeling?

1058
00:57:54,200 --> 00:57:55,760
Only about as good as I look.

1059
00:57:56,600 --> 00:57:57,480
What happened?

1060
00:57:57,520 --> 00:57:59,000
Well, I was hoping
you could help me with that.

1061
00:57:59,640 --> 00:58:00,720
Are you okay to talk?

1062
00:58:02,080 --> 00:58:02,960
Yeah.

1063
00:58:04,040 --> 00:58:05,560
I don't know how much use
I'm gonna be, but...

1064
00:58:05,600 --> 00:58:08,280
Well, you've been unconscious
for almost a week.

1065
00:58:08,520 --> 00:58:09,560
Wait, what?

1066
00:58:09,800 --> 00:58:10,920
Where...where is everybody?

1067
00:58:10,960 --> 00:58:12,560
-Do they know I'm all right?
-Yes, they know.

1068
00:58:13,000 --> 00:58:14,880
Maya, Amanda, your father,...

1069
00:58:14,920 --> 00:58:16,280
...they've been here
every single day.

1070
00:58:16,320 --> 00:58:17,520
Hardly left your side.

1071
00:58:18,640 --> 00:58:20,720
The only reason they're not here
now is by my order.

1072
00:58:21,240 --> 00:58:22,120
Why?

1073
00:58:22,960 --> 00:58:24,600
Because I gotta ask you
a few questions.

1074
00:58:24,960 --> 00:58:25,960
And also...

1075
00:58:27,640 --> 00:58:28,600
While you were under,...

1076
00:58:28,640 --> 00:58:31,960
...someone broke into your room,
pumped your IV full of morphine.

1077
00:58:32,360 --> 00:58:33,400
Enough to kill you.

1078
00:58:33,800 --> 00:58:34,800
Charlie, I need you to think...

1079
00:58:34,840 --> 00:58:36,400
...about that night
of the accident.

1080
00:58:37,320 --> 00:58:38,960
Were you the only one out there?

1081
00:58:40,840 --> 00:58:41,800
I don't know.

1082
00:58:42,800 --> 00:58:45,080
I remember, I, I went to drink.

1083
00:58:46,600 --> 00:58:48,920
Try, please. It's important.

1084
00:58:49,720 --> 00:58:50,760
I remember something...

1085
00:58:52,840 --> 00:58:55,760
Somebody grabbed me, and then,
and then a pain in my arm.

1086
00:58:56,040 --> 00:58:57,800
-Is that from the drugs?
-What?

1087
00:58:57,840 --> 00:58:59,920
Well, doctors said they found
painkillers in your system.

1088
00:58:59,960 --> 00:59:02,120
No, no. I didn't use that night.

1089
00:59:02,720 --> 00:59:04,960
I, I wanted to
and I, I went to, but...

1090
00:59:06,160 --> 00:59:07,360
I couldn't find any.

1091
00:59:08,880 --> 00:59:10,480
Are you saying
somebody drugged you?

1092
00:59:12,560 --> 00:59:13,960
I don't remember anything else.

1093
00:59:17,160 --> 00:59:19,000
What about
the colchicine tablets, Charlie?

1094
00:59:19,240 --> 00:59:20,600
We found them in your car.

1095
00:59:21,480 --> 00:59:23,240
What the heck is colchicine?

1096
00:59:47,120 --> 00:59:48,800
I've seen the way
you look at her.

1097
00:59:59,360 --> 01:00:00,520
So you admit it.

1098
01:00:04,280 --> 01:00:05,800
I just wanted to feel...

1099
01:00:07,360 --> 01:00:08,400
...something...

1100
01:00:10,080 --> 01:00:11,320
...besides the grief.

1101
01:00:14,680 --> 01:00:16,000
But it didn't make me feel
any better.

1102
01:00:16,040 --> 01:00:17,240
Just made me feel more...

1103
01:00:18,600 --> 01:00:19,480
...guilt.

1104
01:00:21,920 --> 01:00:24,600
And that's all I feel anymore
is just grief and guilt.

1105
01:00:28,920 --> 01:00:31,600
Do you really expect me
to feel sorry for you?

1106
01:00:32,040 --> 01:00:33,760
She's Charlie's girlfriend.

1107
01:00:33,800 --> 01:00:36,120
-When Charlie finds out, he's...
-I know, okay?

1108
01:00:36,240 --> 01:00:37,120
I know.

1109
01:00:38,080 --> 01:00:40,400
And it kills me to think about
Charlie...

1110
01:00:40,440 --> 01:00:42,080
...laying there in the hospital
and me...

1111
01:00:44,520 --> 01:00:45,760
...I'm tired, Amanda.

1112
01:00:47,120 --> 01:00:48,480
I'm tired of all the fighting.

1113
01:00:49,720 --> 01:00:51,120
I'm tired about the lying.

1114
01:00:54,240 --> 01:00:55,800
I just want it all to be over.

1115
01:01:05,520 --> 01:01:07,360
You want what to be over?

1116
01:01:08,080 --> 01:01:09,240
You were right...

1117
01:01:10,120 --> 01:01:11,760
...about me all those years ago.

1118
01:01:14,240 --> 01:01:15,520
I cheated on Lauren.

1119
01:01:18,600 --> 01:01:21,960
And it was a stupid,
stupid mistake.

1120
01:01:24,080 --> 01:01:25,320
And I couldn't tell her.

1121
01:01:27,760 --> 01:01:30,080
And I regretted it
every day of my life.

1122
01:01:30,240 --> 01:01:31,400
And now she's...

1123
01:01:34,920 --> 01:01:35,840
...she's gone.

1124
01:01:39,440 --> 01:01:42,600
And I was too much of a coward
to tell her...

1125
01:01:45,600 --> 01:01:47,080
...to tell her how sorry I was...

1126
01:01:50,680 --> 01:01:52,240
...how it ate me up inside.

1127
01:01:55,320 --> 01:01:58,640
I really did love her
despite what you think.

1128
01:02:02,360 --> 01:02:03,720
I loved her more than anything.

1129
01:02:08,000 --> 01:02:09,120
I never meant to hurt her.

1130
01:02:18,440 --> 01:02:19,520
Where are you going?

1131
01:02:24,560 --> 01:02:25,440
Ian?

1132
01:02:35,000 --> 01:02:37,760
<i>-This is Stone.</i>
-Hey, Josh, it's Amanda.

1133
01:02:37,880 --> 01:02:39,240
-Can you talk?
<i>-Yeah.</i>

1134
01:02:39,280 --> 01:02:40,640
<i>I was actually gonna call you.</i>

1135
01:02:40,680 --> 01:02:42,680
<i>I had a talk with Charlie</i>
<i>that was interesting.</i>

1136
01:02:43,280 --> 01:02:45,880
Well, it'll be nothing compared
to what Ian just told me.

1137
01:02:46,320 --> 01:02:48,640
-He admitted to the affair.
<i>-What?</i>

1138
01:02:49,080 --> 01:02:50,440
Oh, you should've seen him...

1139
01:02:50,480 --> 01:02:51,880
...and heard the things
he was saying.

1140
01:02:51,920 --> 01:02:53,080
It was almost like...

1141
01:02:53,560 --> 01:02:55,200
...it was almost like
a confession.

1142
01:02:55,240 --> 01:02:56,520
<i>I'm going to the wellness center.</i>

1143
01:02:56,560 --> 01:02:57,640
<i>Can you meet me there?</i>

1144
01:02:57,960 --> 01:02:58,920
The center?

1145
01:02:58,960 --> 01:03:00,240
-Yeah, but I...
<i>-Good.</i>

1146
01:03:00,280 --> 01:03:01,200
<i>Go now.</i>

1147
01:03:05,080 --> 01:03:06,480
I can't do this anymore.

1148
01:03:08,280 --> 01:03:09,840
I won't be able
to live with myself.

1149
01:03:12,480 --> 01:03:13,680
I understand.

1150
01:03:18,840 --> 01:03:20,440
Did you do what we talked about?

1151
01:03:23,000 --> 01:03:23,880
Yeah.

1152
01:03:24,840 --> 01:03:25,800
I...

1153
01:03:26,360 --> 01:03:28,320
I told her about us...

1154
01:03:31,200 --> 01:03:32,600
...and how I cheated on Lauren.

1155
01:03:33,400 --> 01:03:34,360
Everything.

1156
01:03:40,120 --> 01:03:41,560
I'm really proud of you.

1157
01:03:42,920 --> 01:03:44,000
I know that wasn't easy,...

1158
01:03:44,040 --> 01:03:45,920
...but now you don't have to
carry the guilt.

1159
01:03:48,960 --> 01:03:50,680
And like Lauren always said,...

1160
01:03:51,360 --> 01:03:53,120
...Harmony starts from within.

1161
01:03:53,960 --> 01:03:55,000
So...

1162
01:04:10,360 --> 01:04:11,520
-Hey.
-Hey.

1163
01:04:14,080 --> 01:04:14,960
So, what's going on?

1164
01:04:15,000 --> 01:04:16,520
I need your help finding
something in Ian's office.

1165
01:04:16,560 --> 01:04:17,920
-What?
-I'll explain as we go.

1166
01:04:17,960 --> 01:04:20,280
I need a warrant to search.
But don't you own the business?

1167
01:04:20,320 --> 01:04:21,920
Oh, half, yeah, technically.

1168
01:04:21,960 --> 01:04:23,720
Do I have your permission
to search the premises?

1169
01:04:28,080 --> 01:04:29,520
So, what are we looking for?

1170
01:04:29,560 --> 01:04:31,720
Charlie said he was attacked
the night of the accident.

1171
01:04:31,760 --> 01:04:33,320
Normally, I'd take that
with a grain of salt,...

1172
01:04:33,360 --> 01:04:35,280
...but since he was also attacked
at the hospital,...

1173
01:04:35,320 --> 01:04:36,760
...it lends the story
some credence.

1174
01:04:36,800 --> 01:04:37,920
Well, how did it happen?

1175
01:04:37,960 --> 01:04:40,080
Well, someone drugged him
and pushed him over the ridge.

1176
01:04:40,960 --> 01:04:42,600
And you think his dad did it?

1177
01:04:42,640 --> 01:04:44,400
Well, stranger things
have happened.

1178
01:04:44,440 --> 01:04:46,040
When you told me
about the affair,...

1179
01:04:46,640 --> 01:04:47,640
...thought that sounded like
enough motive...

1180
01:04:47,680 --> 01:04:48,720
...to at least pursue him.

1181
01:04:48,760 --> 01:04:50,280
Now all we need is something
that connects him...

1182
01:04:50,320 --> 01:04:51,320
...to Charlie's accident.

1183
01:04:51,360 --> 01:04:52,320
Is that...

1184
01:05:04,480 --> 01:05:05,840
Looks like we found our weapon.

1185
01:05:10,400 --> 01:05:12,560
-Look.
-Colchicine.

1186
01:05:13,560 --> 01:05:14,520
I'm sorry, Amanda,
looks like you were right...

1187
01:05:14,560 --> 01:05:15,760
...about Ian all along.

1188
01:05:19,200 --> 01:05:20,080
Stone.

1189
01:05:21,280 --> 01:05:22,160
Got it.

1190
01:05:22,720 --> 01:05:23,800
Two shots fired at the house.

1191
01:05:23,840 --> 01:05:24,880
-Let's go.
-What?

1192
01:05:35,400 --> 01:05:37,400
Stay here. Lock the door.

1193
01:06:01,760 --> 01:06:03,000
Is anyone there?

1194
01:06:11,440 --> 01:06:12,320
Hello?

1195
01:06:16,640 --> 01:06:17,800
Is anyone there?

1196
01:06:59,920 --> 01:07:01,200
Maya, what are doing in there?

1197
01:07:01,240 --> 01:07:03,280
-It's Ian.
-It's Ian.

1198
01:07:03,320 --> 01:07:04,560
He...he did this to me.

1199
01:07:04,600 --> 01:07:05,520
We were in the cottage.

1200
01:07:05,560 --> 01:07:07,080
We were talking
and he pulled a gun.

1201
01:07:07,120 --> 01:07:08,800
-He just...
-Okay. Are you okay?

1202
01:07:08,840 --> 01:07:10,200
Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine.

1203
01:07:10,240 --> 01:07:12,120
-Where is Ian now?
-I don't know.

1204
01:07:12,160 --> 01:07:13,280
I, I just took the bat.

1205
01:07:13,320 --> 01:07:14,200
I knocked him out with it...

1206
01:07:14,240 --> 01:07:16,440
-...and then I just ran.
-Okay.

1207
01:07:17,880 --> 01:07:19,280
Was that Amanda?

1208
01:07:21,440 --> 01:07:23,240
-Hey, are you okay?
-Hey. Yeah.

1209
01:07:23,280 --> 01:07:24,560
-He's inside.
-Okay.

1210
01:07:33,680 --> 01:07:34,560
Ian?

1211
01:07:36,680 --> 01:07:37,560
Is he...

1212
01:07:38,520 --> 01:07:39,800
No, he's still alive.

1213
01:07:40,000 --> 01:07:41,240
What? Take it easy.

1214
01:07:41,280 --> 01:07:43,200
-Take it easy.
-What...what's going on?

1215
01:07:43,240 --> 01:07:44,800
What's going on is,
you're under arrest.

1216
01:07:44,840 --> 01:07:46,080
-What?
-I have you on assault...

1217
01:07:46,120 --> 01:07:47,120
...with a deadly weapon,...

1218
01:07:47,160 --> 01:07:48,680
...attempted murder
of your son...

1219
01:07:48,720 --> 01:07:49,800
...and a possible murder
of your wife.

1220
01:07:49,840 --> 01:07:51,200
But this is insane.

1221
01:07:51,520 --> 01:07:52,520
Look, I don't know
what happened here,...

1222
01:07:52,560 --> 01:07:54,360
-...but I, I didn't hurt anyone.
-Let's go.

1223
01:07:55,840 --> 01:07:57,360
Maya, tell him.

1224
01:07:57,760 --> 01:07:59,520
I'm sorry, Ian, you need help.

1225
01:08:00,200 --> 01:08:01,080
Amanda?

1226
01:08:02,080 --> 01:08:04,360
-Please, just take him away.
-What? No.

1227
01:08:04,400 --> 01:08:06,200
No, you're,
you're making a mistake here.

1228
01:08:06,920 --> 01:08:09,040
Amanda, Maya.

1229
01:08:11,440 --> 01:08:12,400
It's over.

1230
01:08:18,400 --> 01:08:20,600
Oh, it's so good
to see you sitting upright.

1231
01:08:20,640 --> 01:08:21,640
It feels good, too.

1232
01:08:22,640 --> 01:08:24,680
I never thought I'd be so anxious
to get out of bed.

1233
01:08:24,720 --> 01:08:25,600
Yeah?

1234
01:08:26,360 --> 01:08:29,080
You still think you'll be able
to come home tomorrow?

1235
01:08:29,120 --> 01:08:30,520
That's what the doctor says.

1236
01:08:31,480 --> 01:08:33,120
Although, I'm not sure how much
it's gonna feel like home...

1237
01:08:33,160 --> 01:08:34,360
...after what you told me.

1238
01:08:34,400 --> 01:08:37,280
Charlie, I'm so sorry
for everything he did.

1239
01:08:37,680 --> 01:08:38,920
It's so hard to believe.

1240
01:08:39,680 --> 01:08:40,560
I know.

1241
01:08:40,880 --> 01:08:43,640
I'm still trying to wrap my brain
around it.

1242
01:08:44,160 --> 01:08:46,400
I mean,
why would he do that to her?

1243
01:08:46,520 --> 01:08:48,440
Or just for some insurance money?

1244
01:08:48,840 --> 01:08:51,920
That and the problems he was
having with Mom, apparently.

1245
01:08:52,640 --> 01:08:54,920
I still can't believe he told you
about the affair.

1246
01:08:54,960 --> 01:08:55,880
Me neither.

1247
01:08:56,240 --> 01:08:58,360
It was a long time coming.

1248
01:08:59,440 --> 01:09:00,680
Do you think there were others?

1249
01:09:03,920 --> 01:09:04,800
I don't know.

1250
01:09:06,000 --> 01:09:08,000
It's possible, I guess.

1251
01:09:10,440 --> 01:09:12,000
I never told mom this, but...

1252
01:09:13,480 --> 01:09:15,960
...I always believed you,
about Dad.

1253
01:09:17,240 --> 01:09:19,000
-You did?
-Yeah. I just...

1254
01:09:19,160 --> 01:09:20,200
I couldn't admit it.

1255
01:09:21,480 --> 01:09:22,840
Do you remember
a few years back,...

1256
01:09:22,880 --> 01:09:24,400
...when there was a vandalism
at the center?

1257
01:09:25,000 --> 01:09:27,400
-Yeah?
-I don't think it was a robbery.

1258
01:09:27,800 --> 01:09:30,840
I think Dad dumped a girl and
she took it out on the office.

1259
01:09:33,000 --> 01:09:34,360
Why are you telling me this?

1260
01:09:34,480 --> 01:09:35,360
Because...

1261
01:09:37,360 --> 01:09:38,760
...I wanted to say I'm sorry.

1262
01:09:40,600 --> 01:09:41,520
That maybe if I did,...

1263
01:09:41,560 --> 01:09:43,120
...things wouldn't have
ended up this way,...

1264
01:09:43,680 --> 01:09:45,440
...that maybe my mom
would've still been here.

1265
01:09:46,360 --> 01:09:47,240
Hey.

1266
01:09:47,680 --> 01:09:49,360
Don't blame yourself for this.

1267
01:09:49,520 --> 01:09:51,480
The only person at fault here
is Ian.

1268
01:09:51,840 --> 01:09:52,720
Okay?

1269
01:09:53,280 --> 01:09:54,160
Yeah.

1270
01:09:55,880 --> 01:09:58,240
All that matters now
is that you're coming home.

1271
01:09:58,960 --> 01:10:00,760
All right, we're gonna
get through this together.

1272
01:10:01,960 --> 01:10:02,840
We're family.

1273
01:10:03,320 --> 01:10:04,400
-Okay?
-All right.

1274
01:10:09,920 --> 01:10:11,280
We really haven't had a chance
to catch up...

1275
01:10:11,320 --> 01:10:12,560
...since the other night.

1276
01:10:13,320 --> 01:10:14,320
Yeah.

1277
01:10:14,880 --> 01:10:15,840
Sorry about that.

1278
01:10:15,880 --> 01:10:16,760
Here you go.

1279
01:10:17,040 --> 01:10:18,480
Yeah, I was fillin' out
a lot of paperwork,...

1280
01:10:18,520 --> 01:10:20,080
...trying to explain
what the heck happened.

1281
01:10:21,280 --> 01:10:22,200
I bet.

1282
01:10:24,240 --> 01:10:25,280
How are you holdin' up?

1283
01:10:26,240 --> 01:10:29,200
A little better.
But still pretty shaken up.

1284
01:10:30,280 --> 01:10:32,600
How about you?
How are things with Ian?

1285
01:10:32,800 --> 01:10:33,920
Just as belligerent.

1286
01:10:34,280 --> 01:10:37,080
Keeps comin' up with every excuse
to deny everything.

1287
01:10:37,280 --> 01:10:39,480
But he can't argue
with the evidence.

1288
01:10:40,160 --> 01:10:42,840
-I know.
-Hey, trust me.

1289
01:10:43,560 --> 01:10:45,240
He's going away for a long time.

1290
01:10:45,640 --> 01:10:47,200
And you can all put this
behind you.

1291
01:10:49,600 --> 01:10:50,920
I hear Charlie's comin' home.

1292
01:10:50,960 --> 01:10:53,320
He is. Yeah.
I just saw him this morning.

1293
01:10:53,360 --> 01:10:55,520
And they cleared him
to leave the hospital tomorrow.

1294
01:10:55,560 --> 01:10:57,120
-Good.
-So it'll be nice...

1295
01:10:57,160 --> 01:10:58,200
...to have him home.

1296
01:10:58,240 --> 01:11:00,320
Nice to make things
feel normal again.

1297
01:11:00,360 --> 01:11:03,440
Well, as normal as possible,
I guess.

1298
01:11:03,800 --> 01:11:04,960
How are things at the center?

1299
01:11:05,000 --> 01:11:06,760
Well, we closed it down
for a few days, you know,...

1300
01:11:06,800 --> 01:11:09,240
...while we try and figure out
what to do next.

1301
01:11:09,520 --> 01:11:12,600
Maya keeps saying that I should
take over instead of selling it.

1302
01:11:13,800 --> 01:11:15,280
And keep her on staff,...

1303
01:11:15,320 --> 01:11:18,240
-...I presume. Yeah.
-Yeah, I, I suppose so.

1304
01:11:19,000 --> 01:11:19,880
I just...

1305
01:11:20,040 --> 01:11:21,040
I never thought that I'd be...

1306
01:11:21,080 --> 01:11:23,280
...taking over Mom and Dad's
place. You know?

1307
01:11:23,520 --> 01:11:26,040
Well, Lauren's place.

1308
01:11:26,760 --> 01:11:27,880
Your place.

1309
01:11:31,400 --> 01:11:35,000
Well, for what it's worth,
I think you should stay.

1310
01:12:15,800 --> 01:12:17,920
Hello? Anybody there?

1311
01:12:59,640 --> 01:13:00,520
Aunt Amanda.

1312
01:13:00,560 --> 01:13:03,000
Hey, Charlie.
I'm sorry for calling so late.

1313
01:13:03,040 --> 01:13:04,960
-If you can't talk...
-No, no, it's okay,...

1314
01:13:05,000 --> 01:13:07,360
...the nurses have eased up on me
since it's my last day.

1315
01:13:07,400 --> 01:13:08,640
-Is everything okay?
-Yeah.

1316
01:13:08,680 --> 01:13:09,960
No, everything's great.

1317
01:13:10,200 --> 01:13:11,560
I just had a quick question.

1318
01:13:11,600 --> 01:13:12,920
Something I'm trying
to figure out.

1319
01:13:12,960 --> 01:13:13,840
Sure.

1320
01:13:13,880 --> 01:13:16,040
The day the colchicine tablets
were ordered,...

1321
01:13:16,080 --> 01:13:17,600
...you were on the computer.

1322
01:13:17,640 --> 01:13:19,760
I saw it on the security camera.

1323
01:13:20,400 --> 01:13:21,280
Okay.

1324
01:13:21,440 --> 01:13:23,240
But if you didn't order
the drugs,...

1325
01:13:23,280 --> 01:13:25,560
...then why were you
on the computer?

1326
01:13:25,600 --> 01:13:27,880
And I'm, I promise,
I'm not accusing you of anything.

1327
01:13:27,920 --> 01:13:30,040
I'm just trying to make sense
of it is all.

1328
01:13:30,080 --> 01:13:31,480
No, no, no, it's,
it's totally fine.

1329
01:13:31,520 --> 01:13:34,360
I, I get it. But ho...honestly,
I can't remember.

1330
01:13:34,920 --> 01:13:36,600
Okay, please try.

1331
01:13:36,640 --> 01:13:38,960
It would have been a few days
before the reopening.

1332
01:13:40,760 --> 01:13:43,560
Remember the night when your mom
asked me to join the business?

1333
01:13:43,600 --> 01:13:45,720
The order was placed
the following day.

1334
01:13:45,760 --> 01:13:47,280
Oh, wait.

1335
01:13:48,280 --> 01:13:50,520
That was the night
Mom started feeling nauseous.

1336
01:13:50,560 --> 01:13:51,680
Maya was looking after her,...

1337
01:13:51,720 --> 01:13:53,920
...so she asked me to check
the schedule on the computer.

1338
01:13:55,360 --> 01:13:58,120
What? Maya asked you
to use the computer?

1339
01:13:58,160 --> 01:13:59,440
<i>Yeah. Why?</i>

1340
01:14:02,360 --> 01:14:03,240
Hello?

1341
01:14:04,480 --> 01:14:05,520
Auntie Amanda?

1342
01:14:24,000 --> 01:14:25,880
Oh, good. You're awake.

1343
01:14:47,440 --> 01:14:48,320
Wha...

1344
01:14:48,440 --> 01:14:50,640
Maya, why are you doing this?

1345
01:14:51,600 --> 01:14:53,040
I didn't want this.

1346
01:14:53,280 --> 01:14:54,760
None of this
was supposed to happen.

1347
01:14:54,800 --> 01:14:56,480
Nobody was supposed to get hurt.

1348
01:14:56,520 --> 01:14:58,120
Nobody was supposed to die.

1349
01:14:58,160 --> 01:15:02,600
And then you came here
and ruined everything.

1350
01:15:04,720 --> 01:15:06,600
Just like you did
three years ago.

1351
01:15:07,400 --> 01:15:09,560
It was, it was you.

1352
01:15:10,000 --> 01:15:12,160
You're the one that Ian
had the affair with.

1353
01:15:12,200 --> 01:15:16,240
Yes, and everything was fine
and then you told Lauren.

1354
01:15:16,280 --> 01:15:18,080
And then Ian made it stop.

1355
01:15:18,120 --> 01:15:21,000
That's why you killed Lauren?
Because Ian broke it off?

1356
01:15:21,040 --> 01:15:23,160
No, I didn't mean to kill her!

1357
01:15:24,440 --> 01:15:26,840
I just started work here
to spite him.

1358
01:15:27,080 --> 01:15:29,600
He wanted me to leave it,
but then I fell for Charlie.

1359
01:15:29,960 --> 01:15:32,440
Oh, gosh.
Lauren was so nice to me.

1360
01:15:32,960 --> 01:15:34,880
She took me under her wing.

1361
01:15:35,120 --> 01:15:37,840
She trusted me,
she was grooming me,...

1362
01:15:38,400 --> 01:15:40,320
...relying on me.

1363
01:15:41,000 --> 01:15:42,360
And then you showed up.

1364
01:15:42,520 --> 01:15:45,240
And she...she just gives you
half the company.

1365
01:15:45,280 --> 01:15:47,200
That's not fair.

1366
01:15:47,240 --> 01:15:50,080
If you cared for Lauren so much,
why did you kill her?

1367
01:15:50,120 --> 01:15:53,480
I didn't mean to kill her.

1368
01:15:53,920 --> 01:15:56,120
I just wanted her to get sick.

1369
01:15:57,360 --> 01:16:00,400
I just wanted to take charge
while she recovered...

1370
01:16:00,440 --> 01:16:05,120
...and show her I deserve
to be here and not you.

1371
01:16:05,640 --> 01:16:07,040
It wasn't just Lauren.

1372
01:16:07,400 --> 01:16:08,680
You hurt Charlie.

1373
01:16:09,440 --> 01:16:11,400
And you framed Ian, too,
didn't you?

1374
01:16:11,680 --> 01:16:13,200
Planted the pills in his office?

1375
01:16:13,240 --> 01:16:15,680
You didn't give me a choice.

1376
01:16:15,720 --> 01:16:17,840
After everything
she did for you...

1377
01:16:18,560 --> 01:16:20,960
Lauren was nothing
but compassionate.

1378
01:16:21,400 --> 01:16:24,040
Tried to help you, but you,...

1379
01:16:24,160 --> 01:16:26,680
...you kill her and
you destroyed everything...

1380
01:16:26,720 --> 01:16:27,840
...she ever cared about.

1381
01:16:27,880 --> 01:16:29,120
Because of you!

1382
01:16:30,240 --> 01:16:31,680
Because of you!

1383
01:16:32,200 --> 01:16:35,840
You kept the detective going
and investigating.

1384
01:16:35,880 --> 01:16:38,360
I wasn't gonna lose
everything,...

1385
01:16:38,400 --> 01:16:39,720
...go to jail
for the rest of my life...

1386
01:16:39,760 --> 01:16:41,600
...because of one stupid mistake.

1387
01:16:41,640 --> 01:16:43,120
Do you understand that?

1388
01:16:43,160 --> 01:16:44,880
-You're a monster.
-No.

1389
01:16:44,920 --> 01:16:47,120
Well, unfortunately for you,...

1390
01:16:47,520 --> 01:16:49,320
...you're the only one
that thinks that.

1391
01:16:51,880 --> 01:16:52,840
No! No!

1392
01:17:03,680 --> 01:17:04,760
No.

1393
01:17:16,320 --> 01:17:19,600
For what it's worth,
I really am sorry.

1394
01:17:19,840 --> 01:17:20,800
Maya, please.

1395
01:17:20,840 --> 01:17:22,320
You don't have to do this.

1396
01:17:22,440 --> 01:17:23,760
Yes, I do.

1397
01:17:23,960 --> 01:17:25,160
But don't worry.

1398
01:17:25,560 --> 01:17:27,440
I'll take care of Charlie...

1399
01:17:28,080 --> 01:17:30,040
...and I'll carry on
Lauren's legacy.

1400
01:17:30,560 --> 01:17:33,320
<i>Close your eyes and visualize.</i>

1401
01:17:53,400 --> 01:17:56,240
<i>Find a place</i>
<i>that brings you comfort.</i>

1402
01:18:01,880 --> 01:18:05,840
<i>Let calm wash over you and</i>
<i>let everything just disappear.</i>

1403
01:18:08,080 --> 01:18:09,480
<i>Good.</i>

1404
01:18:18,600 --> 01:18:19,680
-Hey!
-Hey!

1405
01:18:20,160 --> 01:18:22,280
So, how's the new instructor?

1406
01:18:22,320 --> 01:18:23,400
She's good.

1407
01:18:23,440 --> 01:18:26,880
I mean, she's no Lauren,
but who is?

1408
01:18:27,400 --> 01:18:28,280
Hey, thanks for all your help...

1409
01:18:28,320 --> 01:18:29,720
-...around here, Charlie.
-Yeah.

1410
01:18:29,760 --> 01:18:31,360
I wouldn't be able to
run the place without you.

1411
01:18:31,400 --> 01:18:32,560
I'm really enjoying it.

1412
01:18:32,840 --> 01:18:35,000
And the view
ain't so bad, either.

1413
01:18:35,040 --> 01:18:37,640
You...you just work on
your inner peace, okay?

1414
01:18:46,480 --> 01:18:47,360
Hey.

1415
01:18:48,120 --> 01:18:49,080
Hey.

1416
01:18:49,880 --> 01:18:54,160
I just wanted to say I'm sorry
for how I treated you...

1417
01:18:55,200 --> 01:18:56,360
...and for what I did.

1418
01:18:57,800 --> 01:19:00,440
I'm, I'm sorry, too,...

1419
01:19:01,120 --> 01:19:02,720
...for thinking
you could have done it.

1420
01:19:03,880 --> 01:19:06,520
I, I just wanna move forward.

1421
01:19:06,960 --> 01:19:08,920
I'm still working on
forgiving you...

1422
01:19:08,960 --> 01:19:10,480
...for everything with Maya,...

1423
01:19:10,840 --> 01:19:11,880
...but...

1424
01:19:12,480 --> 01:19:15,400
...I'm, I'm tired of being angry.

1425
01:19:16,240 --> 01:19:17,240
Yeah, me, too.

1426
01:19:18,960 --> 01:19:20,200
I'd like to give it a shot.

1427
01:19:21,800 --> 01:19:22,680
Me, too.

1428
01:19:26,840 --> 01:19:27,840
Hey, buddy.

1429
01:19:36,720 --> 01:19:39,680
So are you gonna tell
Ian and Maya?

1430
01:19:40,480 --> 01:19:41,480
Nah.

1431
01:19:41,760 --> 01:19:43,280
I've done that once before...

1432
01:19:43,320 --> 01:19:46,040
...and all I did was
tear the family apart.

1433
01:19:46,400 --> 01:19:49,120
He never had a chance
to ask Lauren for forgiveness.

1434
01:19:49,160 --> 01:19:51,760
So now's his chance with Charlie.

1435
01:19:53,400 --> 01:19:54,280
So...

1436
01:19:54,800 --> 01:19:56,160
...you decide if you're stayin'?

1437
01:19:56,920 --> 01:19:58,880
It looks that way.

1438
01:19:59,680 --> 01:20:02,600
I'm gonna run the center
with Ian and Charlie.

1439
01:20:02,640 --> 01:20:05,200
And just a fresh new start.

1440
01:20:06,040 --> 01:20:07,760
I think Lauren would be proud.

1441
01:20:08,680 --> 01:20:09,560
Yeah.

1442
01:20:11,080 --> 01:20:12,440
<i>Feel the calm.</i>

1443
01:20:12,800 --> 01:20:14,680
<i>Feel the air around you.</i>

1444
01:20:15,280 --> 01:20:16,760
<i>Let go of your past.</i>

1445
01:20:17,320 --> 01:20:19,120
<i>The future is not here yet.</i>

1446
01:20:19,600 --> 01:20:24,120
<i>Just be in the present</i>
<i>with your breath and your calm.</i>

1447
01:20:30,680 --> 01:20:32,680
<i>Let go of your surroundings.</i>

1448
01:20:32,720 --> 01:20:35,040
<i>Let go of all material things.</i>

1449
01:20:35,560 --> 01:20:39,560
<i>Allow yourself peace and calm.</i>

1450
01:20:41,000 --> 01:20:42,760
<i>Let the past retreat.</i>

1451
01:20:44,040 --> 01:20:46,240
<i>Be here in the moment.</i>

1452
01:20:48,800 --> 01:20:50,320
<i>Good.</i>

